description:
&lt;p&gt;Band 4 PA narrative&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in the Eastbourne Assessment and Treatment Service for a part-time medical PA for a 12month fixed term contract or secondment to cover maternity leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: 30 hours per week - between Monday-Friday 0830-1700.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work as PA to a Consultant Psychiatrist and provide support to the multi-disciplinary team. The team is friendly and dynamic and we are committed to providing excellent care to our Service Users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be enthusiastic, well organised and efficient, self-motivated and have excellent secretarial skills. Preferably you will have had experience in a medical setting or extensive secretarial experience gained elsewhere. You will have an RSAIII or equivalent qualification and/or proven audio typing experience, producing work with a high level of accuracy and attention to detail. You will need to have well developed communication and time management skills. An ability to prioritise effectively in a busy environment is essential. You will need to be adaptable to the needs of the Service and determined to add value to the organisation. Supervisory experience is desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be proficient in the use of Microsoft Office including Word, Excel and Outlook. Experience in the use of databases is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Janice Coker&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Admin Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: janice.coker@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01323 747224&lt;/p&gt;
